*   Trump World Golf Club, Dubai: A second course under construction by Damac, its opening was delayed until at least 2022.

#### Real Estate Licensing

Many developers pay Donald Trump to market their properties and lend their name to projects. Consequently, Trump does not directly own many of the buildings bearing his name. Forbes valued this segment of his business at $562 million, with 33 licensing projects in development, including seven Trump International Hotel and Tower developments. Trump has generated over $74 million in licensing deals and holds $823.3 million in joint venture real estate.

##### Manhattan

*   [Trump Palace](/Trump_Palace), 200 East 69th Street.
*   [Trump Parc](/Trump_Parc) and Trump Parc East: Adjacent buildings on Central Park South.
*   [Trump Plaza](/Trump_Plaza_(New_York_City)), 167 East 61st Street.
*   610 Park Avenue: Trump is involved in the development of this property for [Colony NorthStar](/Colony_NorthStar).
*   Trump SoHo: Originally a partnership with [Bayrock Group](/Bayrock_Group), this hotel was rebranded as [The Dominick](/The_Dominick) after the Trump Organization exited the project. [Felix Sater](/Felix_Sater), linked to Bayrock, was involved in its formation.

##### New York City Suburbs

*   [Trump Bay Street](/Trump_Bay_Street): A rental apartment building in Jersey City, developed with [Kushner Properties](/Kushner_Properties) and The KABR Group.
*   [Trump Plaza (Jersey City)](/Trump_Plaza_(Jersey_City)): An adjacent apartment tower.
*   [Trump Plaza (New Rochelle)](/Trump_Plaza_(New_Rochelle)): A luxury residence and hotel development in Westchester County, NY.
*   [Trump Tower at City Center](/Trump_Tower_(White_Plains)): A condominium apartment building in Westchester County.
*   [Trump Parc Stamford](/Trump_Parc_Stamford): A development in [Stamford, Connecticut](/Stamford,_Connecticut).
